cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with modeling and analyzing an IoT network that harvests RF energy and receives information from the same wireless network. The paper focuses on characterizing two performance metrics related to energy coverage and signal-to-interference-plus-noise and energy coverage. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper also deals with system design insights, which could place it in the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
